                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1462: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-24T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 24, 1932—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 24—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>268. Hankow’s February 23, 4 p.m., regarding protection of Lutheran United
                    Mission at Kwangchow, Honan. Legation has telegraphically instructed
                        <persName>Peck</persName> to make formal representations in the premises to
                    the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>For the Minister:</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
